@Node "maud.datatype()" "maud.datatype/maud.datatype"

@{b}    NAME@{ub}
	maud.datatype -- data type for maud sounds.

@{b}    FUNCTION@{ub}
	The maud data type, a sub-class of the @{"sound.datatype" Link "sound_dtc/sound.datatype()"}, is used
	to load and save maud files.

@{b}    METHODS@{ub}
	OM_NEW -- Create a new sound object from a maud file. Creating an
            empty object (DTST_RAM) is also supported and allows you to create
            an maud files.

        DTM_WRITE -- For DTWM_RAW an maud file will be created. DTWM_IFF is
	    passed to the superclass.

@{b}    BUGS@{ub}
        Supports maud files with either one or two channels and 8 or 16bits.
	The following compression are known to the datatype: ulaw, alaw

@{b}    SEE ALSO@{ub}
	@{"sound.datatype" Link "sound_dtc/sound.datatype()"}.

@EndNode

